3.2.

Por definici√≥n 3.4, sea \[k+\dfrac{k}{2}+\dfrac{k}{3}+\dfrac{k}{4}=1 \quad \Longrightarrow \quad k=\dfrac{12}{25}\]

entonces la funci√≥n de probabilidad de una variable aleatoria discreta \(X\) estar√° dada por:

\[p(x) = \left\{\begin{array}{rcl} \dfrac{12}{25}&si&x=1\\\\ \dfrac{6}{25}&si&x=2\\\\ \dfrac{4}{25}&si&x=3\\\\ \dfrac{3}{25}&si&x=4\\ \end{array}\right.\]

As√≠, la probabilidad de \(P(1\leq X \leq 3)\) ser√°, \[P(1\leq X \leq 3) = 1 - P(X=4) = 1 - \dfrac{3}{25} = \dfrac{22}{25} = 1.88\]

3.3.

a)

Seg√∫n la definici√≥n 3.6 se tiene, \[\int_{-x}^x kx^2\; dx = \int_{-1}^1 kx^2\; dx = 1 \quad \Longrightarrow \quad k=\dfrac{3}{2}\]

integrate(function(x) 3/2*x^2, lower = -1, upper = 1)
## 1 with absolute error < 1.1e-14

b)

\[P(X\leq x) = \int_{-\infty}^x f(t)\; dt = \int_{-\infty}^{-1} 0\; dt + \int_{-1}^x \dfrac{3}{2}t^2\; dt = \dfrac{3}{2} \cdot \dfrac{x^3+1}{3} =\dfrac{x^3+1}{2}\]

funcdist <- function(x) (x^3+1)/2

\[P(X\leq x) = \left\{\begin{array}{rcl} \dfrac{x^3+1}{2}&si&x>0\\\\ 0&si&\mbox{Para cualquier otro valor}\\\\ \end{array}\right.\]

ggplot() +
   xlim(-1, 1) +
   geom_function(
     aes(color = "Normal"),
     fun =~ (.x^3-1)/2 
     )

c)

\[P(X\geq 1/2) = 1 - P(X\leq 1/2) = 1 - \dfrac{x^3+1}{2} = 1 - \dfrac{\left(1/2\right)^3+1}{2} =1- \dfrac{9/8}{2} = \dfrac{7}{16}\]

1-funcdist(1/2)
## [1] 0.4375

\[P(-1/2 \leq X \leq 1/2) = P(X\leq 1/2) - P(X\leq -1/2) = \dfrac{(1/2)^3}{2} - \dfrac{(-1/2)^3}{2} = \dfrac{1}{8} \]

# primera manera
funcdist(1/2) - funcdist(-1/2)
## [1] 0.125
# segunda manera
integrate(function(x) 3/2*x^2, lower = -1/2, upper = 1/2)
## 0.125 with absolute error < 1.4e-15

3.4.

a)

Por la definici√≥n 3.6 se tiene y sabiendo que \(x\leq 0\) es cero. \[\int_{-\infty}^\infty k\cdot e^{-x/5}\; dx = \int_0^\infty k\cdot e^{-x/5}\; dx\] Luego igualando a uno, \[\int_0^\infty k\cdot e^{-x/5}\; dx = 1 \quad \Longrightarrow \quad k = \dfrac{1}{5}\]

integrate(function(x) 1/5 * exp(-x/5), lower = 0, upper = Inf)
## 1 with absolute error < 2e-07

b)

ggplot() +
   xlim(-1, 1) +
   geom_function(
     aes(color = "Normal"),
     fun =~ 1/5 * exp(-.x/5)  
     )

c)

\[P(X\leq 5) = \int_0^5 \dfrac{1}{5}e^{-x/5}\; dx = 1-\dfrac{1}{e}\]

integrate(function(x) 1/5 * exp(-x/5), lower = 0, upper = 5)
## 0.6321206 with absolute error < 7e-15

\[P(0\leq X \leq 8) = \int_0^8 \dfrac{1}{5}e^{-x/5}\; dx = 1-\dfrac{1}{e^{8/5}}\]

integrate(function(x) 1/5 * exp(-x/5), lower = 0, upper = 8)
## 0.7981035 with absolute error < 8.9e-15

d)

La funci√≥n de distribuci√≥n acumulativa esta dado por \[F(x) = \int_{\infty}^x f(t)\; dt = \int_{-\infty}^0 0\; dt + \dfrac{1}{5}\int_0^x e^{-t/5}\; dt = -e^{-x/5}-1\]

ggplot() +
   xlim(0, 10) +
   geom_function(
     aes(color = "Normal"),
     fun =~ -exp(-.x/5) - 1  
     )

3.6

Funci√≥n acumulada de v.a. es \[F(X) = \left\{ \begin{array}{lr} 0&x<0\\ 2x-x^2&0<x<1\\ 1&x>1\\ \end{array}\right.\]

a)

# gr√°fico de F(x)
ggplot() +
   xlim(0, 1) +
   geom_function(
     aes(color = "Normal"),
     fun =~ 2*.x - .x^2,
     )

b)

\(P(X<1/2) = 2\cdot 1/2 - (1/2)^2 = 3/4 = 0.75\)

func <- function(x) 2*x - x^2
func(0.5)
## [1] 0.75

\(1 - P(X>3/4) = 1 - ( 2\cdot 3/4 - (3/4)^2 ) = 1 - (-3/4) 1 - (15/16) = 1/16 = 0.0625\)

1-func(3/4)
## [1] 0.0625

c)

\(F^{'}(x) = 2 x - 2^2 2 - x\)
